{
  "stem": "2004.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were put up in a sort of-- in an abandoned building there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we were taken out every morning to the mountains to build some kind of a dam.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was actually-- that place was hell on Earth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was hell on Earth because we were continuously guarded, not so much by our own Jewish sort of foremen, but we were actually guarded by the SS.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And there was two or three young SS men-- very, very vicious.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they used to beat the living hell out of us-- very, very brutal.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I, fortunately, did not get beaten up that often.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I may have beaten-- beaten up once or twice, not all that severely.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But some of my friends I was with-- they were really beaten up severely.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Any time these young SS had a bad night, they took it out on us, for no reason whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In any event, we were there for several months.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that dam, by the way, never, ever worked.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They tried to divert the water.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They finally gave up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So what they finally did-- they says, to hell with it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they took us and they shipped us right back to Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now I'm back in Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We are already in the summer of 1943.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Plaszow is being, for some reason, slowly liquidated.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So no-- I am in Plaszow no more than maybe three or four weeks after we return from that labor camp in Zakopane, and they load us up on trains, and we're being shipped either into Germany or Austria.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was not known to us at the time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They loaded us up on trains, and we're being shipped to-- we are on the train.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
